me melee, who wants it for a twink.<br><br><br>I play a 58 enchanter, and I frequently get tells to join Guardian groups. And xp in seblis is not worth my effort when I can just walk over to Velks or Chardok.<br>Whenever I get a tell from someone asking, I ask very simply what is the loot method. Now, this may sound like I am a greedy sonofabitz, but at 58, guardian camp is not worth my time for xp. And the only motivation for me going there is loot, and blue diamonds (see the &quot;loot&quot; part.)<br>If I am told &quot;NBFG,&quot; I say &quot;sure, so long as I get the first BD that drops.&quot;<br><br>Now, melees might not think that is fair, but I am basically calling &quot;NBFG&quot; on any BD's that drop. If people think its fair to call NBFG on the lamy or beetle mask, then its sure as hell fine for me to call NBFG on a BD.<br><br>So, in closing, NBFG is *NOT* a *FAIR* method of loot distribution, because it means that int casters (and to a lesser degree wis casters in a fewer areas) will not even be elligable to get pocket lint.<br><br><br>Now, I'd like to say that every single item I have won that I could not use, I have given to another group member who did not win the roll.<br>For example 2x Chrystal Chitin Armbands (velks), Fungi-Tunic (seb), and Bonecaster Robe (Seb).<br><br>Unless I am in a guild group, or a group of individuals who I consider friends, I prefer rolling, since that way, I know loot is fair.<br><br><br>p.s. I've seen someone in guardian call NBFG on 2 lammys, and a beetle mask in the same group. Sounds cool don't it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umredsuperstar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MrEd Superstar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MrEd MiniTank!</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#333333>(12